00:00:21.650 --> 00:00:24.200
PROFESSOR: It's
time to get started.

00:00:24.200 --> 00:00:27.040
Today, we'll complete
our discussion

00:00:27.040 --> 00:00:30.020
of nuclear magnetic resonance.

00:00:30.020 --> 00:00:32.290
And we started that last time.

00:00:32.290 --> 00:00:38.020
And after that, we will talk
about multi-particle states,

00:00:38.020 --> 00:00:40.860
the kind of quantum
mechanical states

00:00:40.860 --> 00:00:45.840
that you need if your system
has more than one particle.

00:00:45.840 --> 00:00:48.460
That will bring us
naturally to the idea

00:00:48.460 --> 00:00:52.260
of denser products of
vector spaces, which

00:00:52.260 --> 00:00:57.910
is the key mathematical
idea behind operations

00:00:57.910 --> 00:01:01.870
such as addition of
angular momentum.

00:01:01.870 --> 00:01:05.980
By introducing a little
before, we really

00:01:05.980 --> 00:01:08.460
talk about addition
of angular momentum,

00:01:08.460 --> 00:01:13.350
the idea of denser
products of vector spaces.

00:01:13.350 --> 00:01:16.860
I really hope that
this subject will

00:01:16.860 --> 00:01:20.130
look a lot less mysterious
in a couple of weeks

00:01:20.130 --> 00:01:24.020
when we will really be
adding angular momentum.

00:01:24.020 --> 00:01:31.000
So you will have seen the
main mathematical structures.

00:01:31.000 --> 00:01:32.790
And you will know
what you're supposed

00:01:32.790 --> 00:01:34.350
to do when you have a formula.

00:01:34.350 --> 00:01:37.110
So that should be of some help.

00:01:37.110 --> 00:01:40.140
So last time, we
were talking about

00:01:40.140 --> 00:01:41.770
nuclear magnetic resonance.

00:01:41.770 --> 00:01:43.200
And I described the problem.

00:01:43.200 --> 00:01:48.110
Here is a summary of where
more or less we got last time.

00:01:48.110 --> 00:01:51.970
We said in the set up for
nuclear magnetic resonance,

00:01:51.970 --> 00:01:57.250
we have a large magnetic field,
the longitudinal magnetic field

00:01:57.250 --> 00:02:01.070
it's sometimes called,
along the z direction.

00:02:01.070 --> 00:02:04.860
In addition to that
longitudinal magnetic field,

00:02:04.860 --> 00:02:09.289
there's a rotating magnetic
field in the xy plane.

00:02:09.289 --> 00:02:12.835
And it's rotating in the
direction that you see here.

00:02:12.835 --> 00:02:20.350
As seen on the xy plane,
it's clockwise on the plane.

00:02:20.350 --> 00:02:23.470
In terms of a rotation
around the z direction,

00:02:23.470 --> 00:02:26.810
it's negative in the sense
that the positive rotation

00:02:26.810 --> 00:02:30.484
around the z plane
would go like this.

00:02:30.484 --> 00:02:32.787
And this magnetic
field is rotating

00:02:32.787 --> 00:02:34.020
in the other direction.

00:02:34.020 --> 00:02:35.390
So I wrote it here.

00:02:35.390 --> 00:02:42.820
The magnitude of this radio
frequency component is B1.

00:02:42.820 --> 00:02:47.080
And typically, it's
much smaller than B0

00:02:47.080 --> 00:02:49.880
in the problems of interest.

00:02:49.880 --> 00:02:54.310
Then, as you recall,
the spin Hamiltonian

00:02:54.310 --> 00:02:58.490
is always given by this
constant gamma that

00:02:58.490 --> 00:03:02.960
relates to the dipole moment of
a particle to its spin angular

00:03:02.960 --> 00:03:09.260
momentum B dot S,
the S operator.

00:03:09.260 --> 00:03:11.440
And the S operator
has components

00:03:11.440 --> 00:03:17.270
Sx, Sy, Sz multiplied by
B. Well, the z component

00:03:17.270 --> 00:03:23.172
picks up a z, the x component
Sx, the y component Sy.

00:03:23.172 --> 00:03:24.380
And this is your Hamiltonian.

00:03:24.380 --> 00:03:28.510
And as we emphasized last
time, this Hamiltonian

00:03:28.510 --> 00:03:30.880
is time dependent.

00:03:30.880 --> 00:03:35.090
Moreover, at different times,
the Hamiltonians don't commute.

00:03:35.090 --> 00:03:41.370
So the HS at time T1, HS at
time T2, they don't commute.

00:03:41.370 --> 00:03:45.770
Therefore, any of the formulas
we have for solving problems

00:03:45.770 --> 00:03:47.325
like this don't apply.

00:03:49.850 --> 00:03:53.860
The only formula that applies
is this time ordered exponential

00:03:53.860 --> 00:03:56.610
that we spoke about
that in general

00:03:56.610 --> 00:03:58.500
is very difficult to use.

00:03:58.500 --> 00:04:01.770
The time ordered exponential
just never quits.

00:04:01.770 --> 00:04:05.520
And we're writing
terms, term after term.

00:04:05.520 --> 00:04:08.100
And then, you have
to add it all up.

00:04:08.100 --> 00:04:10.110
And adding it all
up is difficult.

00:04:10.110 --> 00:04:14.960
So most of the time,
it's not a great help.

00:04:14.960 --> 00:04:18.680
So what did we say we would do?

00:04:18.680 --> 00:04:22.870
We wondered if we could
somehow do quantum mechanics,

00:04:22.870 --> 00:04:26.760
or think of quantum mechanics,
in the rotating frame,

00:04:26.760 --> 00:04:31.600
in a frame that is rotating with
a magnetic field in such a way

00:04:31.600 --> 00:04:36.460
that perhaps in that frame
the physics would simplify.

00:04:36.460 --> 00:04:39.830
And physics simplified would
be that the Hamiltonian becomes

00:04:39.830 --> 00:04:41.030
time independent.

00:04:41.030 --> 00:04:44.740
So we're trying to figure
out, how would the Hamiltonian

00:04:44.740 --> 00:04:47.720
look in another frame?

00:04:47.720 --> 00:04:53.380
Now, we've not discussed
in general very explicitly

00:04:53.380 --> 00:04:56.620
transformations of Hamiltonians
within different frames.

00:04:56.620 --> 00:04:59.750
But we can sort of
roughly try to guess

00:04:59.750 --> 00:05:02.320
what it would have to do.

00:05:02.320 --> 00:05:04.490
So what we said
last time is that we

00:05:04.490 --> 00:05:08.380
would imagine that you
have an original system

00:05:08.380 --> 00:05:11.650
and no magnetic field,
nothing whatsoever.

00:05:11.650 --> 00:05:15.000
So forget about all
that-- no magnetic field.

00:05:15.000 --> 00:05:16.630
You put the spin state.

00:05:16.630 --> 00:05:20.980
It stays there forever,
doesn't precess.

00:05:20.980 --> 00:05:24.480
It doesn't precess because
there's no magnetic field.

00:05:24.480 --> 00:05:27.720
Then, you jump into
a rotating frame.

00:05:27.720 --> 00:05:30.600
So this was a static
frame, no magnetic field.

00:05:30.600 --> 00:05:32.480
And then, you start rotating.

00:05:32.480 --> 00:05:34.220
And then, you look at the spins.

00:05:34.220 --> 00:05:37.680
And the spins are not moving.

00:05:37.680 --> 00:05:40.020
But you say, oh, I'm rotating.

00:05:40.020 --> 00:05:45.425
So for me, they seem to be
precessing, in fact precessing

00:05:45.425 --> 00:05:49.300
with the angular frequency
that I am rotating.

00:05:49.300 --> 00:05:52.800
And therefore, in
my rotating frame,

00:05:52.800 --> 00:05:54.680
I would have a
Hamiltonian that I

00:05:54.680 --> 00:05:59.100
would call the rotating
Hamiltonian, HR.

00:05:59.100 --> 00:06:02.160
And how would it look?

00:06:02.160 --> 00:06:09.960
We claim that in fact spin
states in my rotating frame

00:06:09.960 --> 00:06:13.700
would have to be
rotating really this way.

00:06:13.700 --> 00:06:16.050
Because I'm rotating
with the magnetic field.

00:06:16.050 --> 00:06:19.880
So for me, they're rotating
in the positive z direction

00:06:19.880 --> 00:06:22.430
with angular frequency omega.

00:06:22.430 --> 00:06:24.730
And this would be
the operator that

00:06:24.730 --> 00:06:27.970
makes them rotate
exactly that way.

00:06:27.970 --> 00:06:31.580
Because if you remember,
an operator here minus

00:06:31.580 --> 00:06:36.990
i angle Sz over h
bar, this is the angle

00:06:36.990 --> 00:06:38.530
as a function of time.

00:06:38.530 --> 00:06:43.790
Omega t, that's how these
operators rotate states.

00:06:43.790 --> 00:06:48.720
So this U of t is the
U of t that rotates

00:06:48.720 --> 00:06:52.150
states the way I want
them in my rotating frame.

00:06:52.150 --> 00:06:56.720
Now, you remember for
time independent systems,

00:06:56.720 --> 00:07:04.560
the unitary operator is e
to the minus iht over h bar.

00:07:04.560 --> 00:07:08.340
So you identify the
Hamiltonian as omega Sz.

00:07:13.130 --> 00:07:18.840
In general, given
a unitary operator,

00:07:18.840 --> 00:07:21.120
the Hamiltonian is
obtained this way.

00:07:21.120 --> 00:07:24.620
You take the time derivative
of it multiplied by U dagger.

00:07:24.620 --> 00:07:28.080
And that's the formula for
the Hamiltonian given the time

00:07:28.080 --> 00:07:32.220
evolution operator, something
we did about a couple of weeks

00:07:32.220 --> 00:07:34.640
ago.

00:07:34.640 --> 00:07:39.900
So that's where we stood-- some
idea about the rotating frame.

00:07:39.900 --> 00:07:44.930
So the way we now
make this complete

00:07:44.930 --> 00:07:48.290
is to say, well, I'm going to
attempt to do the following.

00:07:48.290 --> 00:07:59.282
I'm going to act with U, this U
of t, on this complicated state

00:07:59.282 --> 00:08:02.590
that I don't know
how it behaves.

00:08:02.590 --> 00:08:09.100
And this I'm going to call
the rotated wave function.

00:08:09.100 --> 00:08:11.740
It's a definition.

00:08:11.740 --> 00:08:13.800
We're going to use
this operator that

00:08:13.800 --> 00:08:18.200
seems to induce a
rotation of the frames

00:08:18.200 --> 00:08:22.630
and act it on the
state to find this.

00:08:22.630 --> 00:08:25.290
And we're going to hope
that the Schrodinger

00:08:25.290 --> 00:08:29.970
equation for this
one is simpler.

00:08:29.970 --> 00:08:34.239
So actually, last time, I
actually did a computation

00:08:34.239 --> 00:08:36.980
and found what is the
Schrodinger Hamiltonian

00:08:36.980 --> 00:08:43.390
for this, psi R. I want to do
it in a slightly different way.

00:08:43.390 --> 00:08:48.190
I think it's a little easier
perhaps, or maybe less

00:08:48.190 --> 00:08:50.670
familiar but more interesting.

00:08:50.670 --> 00:08:53.300
I write this like that-- U of t.

00:08:53.300 --> 00:08:56.625
And I say, look,
this state evolves

00:08:56.625 --> 00:08:59.470
due to its own Hamiltonian.

00:08:59.470 --> 00:09:01.840
U of t is an extra
thing I've put here.

00:09:01.840 --> 00:09:04.710
So here is U of t.

00:09:04.710 --> 00:09:06.240
But how do I distinguish it?

00:09:06.240 --> 00:09:15.390
I put an S for the spin
system, for HS, psi 0.

00:09:15.390 --> 00:09:22.430
So psi of t is being evolved
by the Schrodinger Hamiltonian,

00:09:22.430 --> 00:09:26.120
the unitary operator
associated to the Hamiltonian

00:09:26.120 --> 00:09:29.030
that we want times time of 0.

00:09:29.030 --> 00:09:34.320
So this is the total
unitary operator

00:09:34.320 --> 00:09:38.660
that evolves this state.

00:09:38.660 --> 00:09:41.490
Therefore, I'm going
to say, I'm going

00:09:41.490 --> 00:09:45.190
to recover the Hamiltonian
using this formula.

00:09:45.190 --> 00:09:51.190
So I will simply say that
the rotating Hamiltonian

00:09:51.190 --> 00:10:04.660
is going to be HR is ih bar
dt of this whole thing, U

00:10:04.660 --> 00:10:11.420
of t US of t, times its dagger.

00:10:11.420 --> 00:10:13.045
Because this is
the general formula

00:10:13.045 --> 00:10:15.180
to obtain the
Hamiltonian when you

00:10:15.180 --> 00:10:17.560
know the time
evolution operator.

00:10:17.560 --> 00:10:24.290
So the dagger of this would
be US dagger U of t dagger.

00:10:27.900 --> 00:10:31.370
Now we have to evaluate
this derivative.

00:10:31.370 --> 00:10:34.410
It's is not all that bad.

00:10:34.410 --> 00:10:37.850
If the time
derivative hits the U,

00:10:37.850 --> 00:10:43.480
this one, then U and U
dagger annihilate each other.

00:10:43.480 --> 00:10:46.170
So you're left with
U dagger of t here.

00:10:46.170 --> 00:10:56.430
So you get ih bar dtU U dagger.

00:10:56.430 --> 00:11:00.640
Now, when it acts on this
second one, what do we get?

00:11:00.640 --> 00:11:02.590
Well, I'll write it this way.

00:11:02.590 --> 00:11:06.860
Plus U of t, because
this will be first.

00:11:06.860 --> 00:11:08.787
Then, ih bar dtUS.

00:11:16.250 --> 00:11:24.260
And then, you have US dagger,
and then U dagger of t.

00:11:30.150 --> 00:11:34.840
Now, this thing is how much?

00:11:34.840 --> 00:11:39.530
Well, in this thing is
in fact this Hamiltonian

00:11:39.530 --> 00:11:45.070
associated to what we called
U, which is just omega Sz.

00:11:48.060 --> 00:11:50.610
So actually, I don't
know if I have-- yeah,

00:11:50.610 --> 00:11:52.370
I have this notation here.

00:11:52.370 --> 00:11:59.570
I think it's useful-- H of
U, the Hamiltonian associated

00:11:59.570 --> 00:12:01.550
to whatever U it is.

00:12:01.550 --> 00:12:07.740
So you get a nice
formula-- plus U of t.

00:12:07.740 --> 00:12:14.941
This is the Hamiltonian
HS U dagger of t.

00:12:17.770 --> 00:12:21.290
So this formula we
derived also last time

00:12:21.290 --> 00:12:29.850
by looking at the differential
equations satisfied by psi R.

00:12:29.850 --> 00:12:32.690
So it's a nice formula.

00:12:32.690 --> 00:12:35.700
If somebody gives you
something like this

00:12:35.700 --> 00:12:37.920
and says, here's a
unitary operator,

00:12:37.920 --> 00:12:40.200
what is the new Hamiltonian?

00:12:40.200 --> 00:12:47.550
The new Hamiltonian is equal to
the transformed old Hamiltonian

00:12:47.550 --> 00:12:51.220
plus the Hamiltonian associated
to this time evolution

00:12:51.220 --> 00:12:52.115
operator.

00:12:52.115 --> 00:12:53.530
It's a nice formula.

00:12:56.190 --> 00:12:59.300
Now, more concretely
now, we can see

00:12:59.300 --> 00:13:01.840
what this is supposed to be.

00:13:01.840 --> 00:13:08.625
So here is the
important crucial step.

00:13:08.625 --> 00:13:13.170
Let's see, HR is
supposed to be what?

00:13:13.170 --> 00:13:18.290
We now know we're going to
choose U to be this thing.

00:13:18.290 --> 00:13:25.050
Therefore, HU is omega Sz hat.

00:13:25.050 --> 00:13:30.540
But now we have U
of t, U dagger of t.

00:13:30.540 --> 00:13:35.720
So I have plus e to
the minus i omega

00:13:35.720 --> 00:13:42.880
tSz over h bar times
the Hamiltonian

00:13:42.880 --> 00:13:47.900
that we have over there,
this full Hamiltonian HS.

00:13:47.900 --> 00:13:49.614
So what is it?

00:13:49.614 --> 00:14:01.050
