00:15:01.510 --> 00:15:05.380
This is the hope that we have.

00:15:05.380 --> 00:15:08.965
Any unitary operator, if
it's what evolves your state,

00:15:08.965 --> 00:15:10.880
it corresponds to Hamiltonian.

00:15:10.880 --> 00:15:14.210
But that's not
anything a priori to do

00:15:14.210 --> 00:15:15.890
with our original Hamiltonian.

00:15:15.890 --> 00:15:18.540
It's just another Hamiltonian.

00:15:18.540 --> 00:15:24.150
So you choose your U of t
behind some Hamiltonian.

00:15:24.150 --> 00:15:26.930
But what you learn is
that the Hamiltonian

00:15:26.930 --> 00:15:30.200
for your new system, or
for the new wave function,

00:15:30.200 --> 00:15:33.136
will involve that
other Hamiltonian.

00:15:33.136 --> 00:15:34.582
Yes?

00:15:34.582 --> 00:15:36.992
