00:38:49.760 --> 00:38:53.750
of this BR.

00:38:53.750 --> 00:39:02.410
So BR is going to be B1 x.

00:39:02.410 --> 00:39:05.030
And then, here is
what's going to happen.

00:39:07.890 --> 00:39:14.130
You have a B1 x here, a B1
over here in the x direction.

00:39:14.130 --> 00:39:18.260
The spin state is sitting
at time equals 0 here.

00:39:21.670 --> 00:39:25.570
And since normal
exponentials that

00:39:25.570 --> 00:39:28.890
do time evolutions
have a minus sign here,

00:39:28.890 --> 00:39:32.910
I claim that instead of
rotating the spin around B1,

00:39:32.910 --> 00:39:35.830
it's really rotating
it around minus B1.

00:39:35.830 --> 00:39:41.650
So the spin will
just go down here.

00:39:41.650 --> 00:39:43.838
Rotate, rotate, rotate, rotate.

00:39:48.050 --> 00:39:57.810
Now, it's rotating with B1,
which is much smaller than B0.

00:39:57.810 --> 00:40:00.610
So it's rotating with
an angular frequency

00:40:00.610 --> 00:40:05.990
that is much smaller than omega
0, but it's rotating down here.

00:40:09.130 --> 00:40:14.935
And now, what's really
happening is the following.

00:40:14.935 --> 00:40:17.590
Let me draw this if I can.

00:40:26.290 --> 00:40:27.800
Here it is.

00:40:27.800 --> 00:40:36.450
The spin is up, and it
begins to go into the y-axis.

00:40:36.450 --> 00:40:37.125
Here is z.

00:40:37.125 --> 00:40:41.940
B1 is turning into the y-axis,
so it rotates a little.

00:40:41.940 --> 00:40:46.880
So let me ask you, what is the
second exponential going to do?

00:40:46.880 --> 00:40:49.400
It's going to rotate it
further, but this time

00:40:49.400 --> 00:40:52.600
around the z-axis.

00:40:52.600 --> 00:40:58.230
So this one goes down a
little bit in some time,

00:40:58.230 --> 00:41:01.250
but then this z exponential,
the other exponential,

00:41:01.250 --> 00:41:03.580
is going to rotate
it around the z-axis.

00:41:03.580 --> 00:41:07.910
So this is going to go
down a little but rotate.

00:41:07.910 --> 00:41:09.630
So actually, what's
going to happen

00:41:09.630 --> 00:41:18.240
is that it's going
to do a spiral.

00:41:18.240 --> 00:41:20.615
As it begins to go down,
the other one rotates.

00:41:20.615 --> 00:41:23.290
It goes down a little,
the other one rotates it.

00:41:23.290 --> 00:41:33.830
In fact, this, since B1 is much
smaller than B0 or omega 0,

00:41:33.830 --> 00:41:36.890
here now, omega is
equal to omega 0,

00:41:36.890 --> 00:41:40.930
so this is rotating around
the z direction with omega 0.

00:41:40.930 --> 00:41:46.910
But B1 is much smaller than B0,
so this rotation is very slow.

00:41:46.910 --> 00:41:50.730
As it goes down a little,
it's rotating very fast

00:41:50.730 --> 00:41:56.990
and fills out the spiral
until it gets down here.

00:41:56.990 --> 00:42:03.880
So that's what the poor
spin is doing in this thing.

00:42:03.880 --> 00:42:09.840
It's actually of
interest to time

00:42:09.840 --> 00:42:15.830
the radio frequency signals,
to time the systems of B1

00:42:15.830 --> 00:42:19.310
so that you get it
to go into the plane

00:42:19.310 --> 00:42:23.350
so that the spin is
maximally perpendicular

00:42:23.350 --> 00:42:25.430
to the original direction.

00:42:25.430 --> 00:42:29.365
For that, you
choose omega 1 times

00:42:29.365 --> 00:42:35.450
time, which is the Larmor
frequency associated

00:42:35.450 --> 00:42:40.390
to B1 times time, to
be equal to pi over 2.

00:42:40.390 --> 00:42:50.110
And omega 1, just like any
omega, is gamma B1 pi over 2.

00:42:50.110 --> 00:42:56.160
So t is pi over 2 gamma B1.

00:42:56.160 --> 00:42:59.890
It's called the half
pulse, something like that.

00:43:05.410 --> 00:43:08.380
No, a 90 degree pulse.

00:43:08.380 --> 00:43:10.330
That's a normal name for it.

00:43:10.330 --> 00:43:13.810
So if you keep the
radio frequency

00:43:13.810 --> 00:43:19.880
on for this much time, then the
spin, at the end of the day,

00:43:19.880 --> 00:43:26.250
it got to the equator of the
sphere, and B1 has disappeared.

00:43:26.250 --> 00:43:29.710
So B1 is gone, BR
is gone, and then

00:43:29.710 --> 00:43:33.475
it keeps rotating because there
is the other magnetic field

00:43:33.475 --> 00:43:38.010
still, the longitudinal
magnetic field.

00:43:38.010 --> 00:43:40.750
One exercise that you
still have in the homework

00:43:40.750 --> 00:43:45.770
is to figure out the equation
of the spiral that comes out

00:43:45.770 --> 00:43:46.430
of here.

00:43:46.430 --> 00:43:50.160
You will find it
sounds complicated,

00:43:50.160 --> 00:43:51.690
but it's a couple of lines.

00:43:51.690 --> 00:43:54.010
It's very simple,
actually, to do it,

00:43:54.010 --> 00:43:56.840
after you think about
it for a second.

00:43:56.840 --> 00:43:59.790
That's one thing
you'll have to do.

00:43:59.790 --> 00:44:04.740
So this, in fact, is basically
the solution of the problem,

00:44:04.740 --> 00:44:07.260
and let's just talk
for a few minutes

00:44:07.260 --> 00:44:10.140
about what it's used for.

00:44:10.140 --> 00:44:13.500
So this is basically
the technique

00:44:13.500 --> 00:44:20.766
that is exactly used for
Magnetic Resonance Imaging,

00:44:20.766 --> 00:44:21.265
MRIs.

00:44:24.590 --> 00:44:28.340
If you have to say one of
the interesting applications

00:44:28.340 --> 00:44:31.490
of quantum mechanics
to technology,

00:44:31.490 --> 00:44:35.910
MRIs, Magnetic
Resonance Imaging,

00:44:35.910 --> 00:44:39.650
is one of the great ones.

00:44:39.650 --> 00:44:42.930
So how does it work?

00:44:42.930 --> 00:44:46.830
Well, it's a very useful device.

00:44:46.830 --> 00:44:50.540
In fact, it
revolutionized medicine

00:44:50.540 --> 00:44:54.130
because it goes much beyond
what you can do with x-rays.

00:44:54.130 --> 00:44:55.660
It's very popular.

00:44:55.660 --> 00:44:59.790
I imagine a good fraction
of you have had an MRI.

00:44:59.790 --> 00:45:00.360
Let's see.

00:45:00.360 --> 00:45:04.160
How many people have had
an MRI in their lives?

00:45:04.160 --> 00:45:09.800
We're pretty much, I
think, 60% of people here.

00:45:09.800 --> 00:45:13.130
So you remember getting
into this cavity?

00:45:13.130 --> 00:45:16.140
Well, you've experienced
there a large--

00:45:16.140 --> 00:45:19.830
if you worry about
cell phone radiation,

00:45:19.830 --> 00:45:22.790
well, there, you
were with two Tesla,

00:45:22.790 --> 00:45:27.350
20,000 Gauss, a big, big magnet.

00:45:27.350 --> 00:45:33.210
It's big enough that it has to
be cooled with liquid helium

00:45:33.210 --> 00:45:37.310
at 3 degrees Kelvin
so you can get

00:45:37.310 --> 00:45:41.810
the currents big enough and
the magnetic field big enough.

00:45:41.810 --> 00:45:51.980
So they put you into this
cylinder, a solenoid,

00:45:51.980 --> 00:45:52.855
and there you go.

00:45:56.360 --> 00:46:00.840
And it's not
dangerous unless you

00:46:00.840 --> 00:46:06.200
forget some metal or
some device like that.

00:46:06.200 --> 00:46:10.710
In fact, it says in
WebMD that if you

00:46:10.710 --> 00:46:15.030
have some sort of tattoos,
they used iron ink,

00:46:15.030 --> 00:46:20.550
it can burn your skin or you
could have some problems.

00:46:20.550 --> 00:46:22.520
Anyway, if you're
claustrophobic,

00:46:22.520 --> 00:46:26.240
may have MRIs that are
open air, but they're

00:46:26.240 --> 00:46:29.500
less powerful, less
strong magnetic field.

00:46:29.500 --> 00:46:33.380
So this is two Tesla, roughly.

00:46:33.380 --> 00:46:39.350
And so what happens
is that basically,

00:46:39.350 --> 00:46:41.910
this thing just is
trying to figure out

00:46:41.910 --> 00:46:44.480
the local
concentration of water.

00:46:44.480 --> 00:46:46.800
It begins like that.

00:46:46.800 --> 00:46:51.530
The magnetic fields react with
the hydrogen atoms, in fact,

00:46:51.530 --> 00:46:54.590
with the protons inside there.

00:46:54.590 --> 00:46:58.310
Each proton has a
magnetic dipole moment.

00:46:58.310 --> 00:47:04.310
It gets roughly aligned to the
magnetic field, to this B0.

00:47:08.760 --> 00:47:13.730
So the protons get
aligned to the B0

00:47:13.730 --> 00:47:17.890
that is going in here, B0.

00:47:17.890 --> 00:47:21.630
So the proton spin is up there.

00:47:21.630 --> 00:47:24.500
In fact, because of
temperature, not all

00:47:24.500 --> 00:47:27.040
of your protons in
your body get aligned.

00:47:27.040 --> 00:47:32.015
Maybe one in a million does,
but that's high enough.

00:47:32.015 --> 00:47:36.400
And then they send
this 90 degree pulse.

00:47:36.400 --> 00:47:39.300
So this thing starts
spiraling, and then

00:47:39.300 --> 00:47:41.840
it finally goes
into this direction

00:47:41.840 --> 00:47:45.440
and it rotates,
rotates like crazy.

00:47:45.440 --> 00:47:51.410
Then, as it rotates like
crazy, a rotating dipole moment

00:47:51.410 --> 00:47:54.420
is like a generator of
electromagnetic waves.

00:47:54.420 --> 00:47:57.400
So it generates an
electromagnetic wave,

00:47:57.400 --> 00:48:03.740
and there are detectors all
over that pick up this signal.

00:48:03.740 --> 00:48:07.230
The strength of that
signal is proportional

00:48:07.230 --> 00:48:10.510
to the concentration of water.

00:48:10.510 --> 00:48:14.480
So it gives you an
idea, not to distinguish

00:48:14.480 --> 00:48:20.935
solid matter versus soft matter,
but all kinds of liquids.

00:48:23.750 --> 00:48:26.860
So it's very, very useful.

00:48:26.860 --> 00:48:30.480
You pick a signal over here
and you get it from a receiver,

00:48:30.480 --> 00:48:34.070
and it tells you about the
local concentration of water.

00:48:34.070 --> 00:48:38.560
And therefore, it allows you to
distinguish different tissues.

00:48:38.560 --> 00:48:42.160
Some tissues have lots of water,
some tissues have less water,

00:48:42.160 --> 00:48:44.535
so it begins to distinguish
different tissues.

00:48:47.090 --> 00:48:50.480
Now, there's two more
things that people do.

00:48:50.480 --> 00:48:58.270
This pin is rotating very fast,
but there's a relaxation time.

00:48:58.270 --> 00:49:02.910
After it rotates
for a while, there's

00:49:02.910 --> 00:49:12.170
a time, T2, is relaxation
of this rotation.

00:49:12.170 --> 00:49:13.990
Relaxation time.

00:49:13.990 --> 00:49:16.600
And then there's
another time, T1,

00:49:16.600 --> 00:49:20.610
which is the time after
this is turned off

00:49:20.610 --> 00:49:25.180
that it takes the
spin to go back

00:49:25.180 --> 00:49:26.810
again to the original position.

00:49:29.830 --> 00:49:33.480
So two times, the
relaxation time

00:49:33.480 --> 00:49:37.340
in which you lose
your rotation here

00:49:37.340 --> 00:49:40.380
because it's interacting
with other spins.

00:49:40.380 --> 00:49:42.850
It's called spin,
spin, relaxation.

00:49:42.850 --> 00:49:48.180
And then an interaction with a
whole set of neighboring atoms

00:49:48.180 --> 00:49:50.740
that brings it
eventually back up

00:49:50.740 --> 00:49:53.440
and aligns it to
the magnetic field.

00:49:53.440 --> 00:49:57.840
So you measure two
things, T1 and T2,

00:49:57.840 --> 00:50:01.260
and those are very
good clues because you

00:50:01.260 --> 00:50:05.000
can put any liquid
in the machine

00:50:05.000 --> 00:50:07.870
and measure its T1 and T2.

00:50:07.870 --> 00:50:11.430
And then you place a table
of T1's and T2's, and then

00:50:11.430 --> 00:50:13.720
if you want to figure
out what kind of thing

00:50:13.720 --> 00:50:16.550
you have in your
body, they look it up,

00:50:16.550 --> 00:50:18.730
and immediately,
they may know what

00:50:18.730 --> 00:50:20.240
are the possible candidates.

00:50:20.240 --> 00:50:27.490
In fact, T2 is actually
enough to distinguish

00:50:27.490 --> 00:50:31.550
white matter, gray matter,
and fluids in your brain.

00:50:31.550 --> 00:50:34.940
Totally different T2's.

00:50:34.940 --> 00:50:41.640
T1 is helpful to discuss
all kinds of things as well.

00:50:41.640 --> 00:50:44.760
So basically, people have
figured out how to do that.

00:50:44.760 --> 00:50:46.570
Finally, one last thing.

00:50:46.570 --> 00:50:51.450
When you go into the machine,
it sometimes makes noises.

00:50:51.450 --> 00:50:53.040
Big noises.

00:50:53.040 --> 00:50:57.530
And those are gradient
magnets that are being moved.

00:50:57.530 --> 00:51:01.320
You see, basically, if this
thing would be like that,

00:51:01.320 --> 00:51:02.940
you would pick up
a signal and you

00:51:02.940 --> 00:51:05.420
wouldn't know where
it comes from.

00:51:05.420 --> 00:51:07.690
So what these
people do now-- this

00:51:07.690 --> 00:51:09.740
has gotten extremely
sophisticated.

00:51:09.740 --> 00:51:15.890
They put a gradient magnet which
changes the value of B0 locally

00:51:15.890 --> 00:51:17.550
by increasing it.

00:51:17.550 --> 00:51:20.540
For example, the B0 is
not really constant in z,

00:51:20.540 --> 00:51:22.270
but it changes.

00:51:22.270 --> 00:51:28.390
So the omega 0 of rotation
of the spins changes as well.

00:51:28.390 --> 00:51:32.650
So with a sufficiently high
gradient of magnetic field,

00:51:32.650 --> 00:51:34.660
they can have
spatial resolution.

00:51:34.660 --> 00:51:37.370
If they pick a signal a
little bit higher frequency,

00:51:37.370 --> 00:51:40.550
they know it's a little
bit higher up in your body.

00:51:40.550 --> 00:51:43.470
So they get resolutions
with these magnets

00:51:43.470 --> 00:51:46.390
of about how much?

00:51:46.390 --> 00:51:48.350
Very high resolutions.

00:51:48.350 --> 00:51:51.290
Half a millimeter.

00:51:51.290 --> 00:51:56.780
So at the end of the day,
it's a great machine,

00:51:56.780 --> 00:52:00.980
and lots of mathematics
in reconstructing images,

00:52:00.980 --> 00:52:05.480
lots of computation, lots
of experimental analysis

00:52:05.480 --> 00:52:08.530
of constants, much of
it phenomenological.

00:52:08.530 --> 00:52:11.930
It would be hard to
predict those constants,

00:52:11.930 --> 00:52:14.260
but you can measure them.

00:52:14.260 --> 00:52:19.090
So it's very, very
practical and very nice.

00:52:19.090 --> 00:52:26.040
So it's a nice application,
and we'll leave it at that.

