00:53:52.310 --> 00:53:56.890
So last part of today's lecture
is multi-particle states

00:53:56.890 --> 00:53:59.520
and tensor products.

00:53:59.520 --> 00:54:03.980
Let's get on with that.

00:54:03.980 --> 00:54:07.600
Let's see we have there.

00:54:07.600 --> 00:54:17.230
So multi-particle states
and tensor products.

00:54:30.030 --> 00:54:31.440
The idea is the following.

00:54:31.440 --> 00:54:33.980
You have a system with
more than one particle.

00:54:33.980 --> 00:54:36.660
Let's talk two particles.

00:54:36.660 --> 00:54:40.030
It won't matter at this
moment whether they're

00:54:40.030 --> 00:54:41.980
distinguishable,
not distinguishable.

00:54:41.980 --> 00:54:43.810
Those are things
that come later,

00:54:43.810 --> 00:54:48.320
and we will probably not discuss
much of that in this semester.

00:54:48.320 --> 00:54:50.880
This will be more in 806.

00:54:50.880 --> 00:54:56.110
But let's consider if
we have particle one,

00:54:56.110 --> 00:54:58.100
and we'll keep the
possibility that this

00:54:58.100 --> 00:55:00.230
is completely
distinguishable, in fact.

00:55:00.230 --> 00:55:03.010
Particle one.

00:55:03.010 --> 00:55:08.810
Its quantum mechanics is
described by a complex vector

00:55:08.810 --> 00:55:22.165
space, v. And you have
some operators, T1, T2.

00:55:25.120 --> 00:55:31.850
Particle two,
complex vector space,

00:55:31.850 --> 00:55:42.300
w, and the operators,
S1, S2, all that.

00:55:42.300 --> 00:55:45.340
You see, the list of
operators is something

00:55:45.340 --> 00:55:48.050
that you are already
familiar with.

00:55:48.050 --> 00:55:52.930
Quantum mechanics operators
can include momentum, position,

00:55:52.930 --> 00:55:57.380
if it's three dimensional,
three positions, three momenta,

00:55:57.380 --> 00:56:04.560
angular momentum, spin,
Hamiltonians, all those things,

00:56:04.560 --> 00:56:08.860
and those exist
for both particles.

00:56:08.860 --> 00:56:13.130
So the question is, how do we
describe the composite system,

00:56:13.130 --> 00:56:17.200
the system of the
two particles that

00:56:17.200 --> 00:56:21.720
exist at the same time, that
possibly could interact even

00:56:21.720 --> 00:56:23.780
with each other?

00:56:23.780 --> 00:56:27.570
So we need a description
of these two things.

00:56:27.570 --> 00:56:32.710
Well, a description
of particle one

00:56:32.710 --> 00:56:37.145
is described by some vector,
v, in the vector space.

00:56:39.950 --> 00:56:45.350
Description of particle two is
some state, some vector omega,

00:56:45.350 --> 00:56:49.330
in the vector space w.

00:56:49.330 --> 00:56:55.820
So we imagine that
it's a reasonable thing

00:56:55.820 --> 00:57:00.200
to give you those two
vectors and say, look,

00:57:00.200 --> 00:57:02.360
that's what particle
one is doing,

00:57:02.360 --> 00:57:06.370
that's what particle two is
doing, and that is correct.

00:57:06.370 --> 00:57:09.330
It's a bit more subtle than
that, as we'll see now,

00:57:09.330 --> 00:57:17.360
but we could list v
and list w, and this

00:57:17.360 --> 00:57:25.345
is the information
about each particle.

00:57:31.970 --> 00:57:38.690
And this is, in some ways,
too naive, as we will see.

00:57:38.690 --> 00:57:44.400
It has the right idea, but
